CTF Challenge: Extract the Flag
Description:
This Python script is designed to solve a Capture The Flag (CTF) challenge by extracting text from an image file. 
The script processes the image to enhance its readability and uses Optical Character Recognition (OCR) to extract the flag.

Instructions:

Input: The provided image file flag1.jpg.
Output: The extracted flag in the format ctf{flag_name}.

Technologies Used:

PIL (Pillow) for image processing
pytesseract for OCR

Features:

Convert the image to grayscale.
Enhance the contrast of the image.
Sharpen the image to improve OCR accuracy.
Extract text from the image using pytesseract.

Setup Instructions:

1. Ensure you have the required packages installed:
bash:
  pip install pytesseract Pillow
2. Place the image file flag1.jpg in the same directory as the script.
3. Run the script:
bash:
  python CTF#1.py
